@startuml
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

left to right direction

title Detailed Backend Request Flow

actor "Client (React App)" as Client

System_Boundary(c1, "WealthTracker Backend (ASP.NET Core)") {
    Component(controller, "API Controller", "C#", "Receives HTTP requests, validates input, and orchestrates the response.")
    Component(service, "Business Service", "C#", "Contains core business logic, data processing, and validation.")
    Component(dbContext, "EF Core DbContext", "C#", "Manages database sessions, queries, and data persistence.")
    database "PostgreSQL DB" as db {
        storage "Tables" as tables
    }
}

Client -> controller: 1. Sends HTTP Request

note top of controller
  - Validates JWT to get User ID.
  - Passes necessary parameters.
end note
controller -> service: 2. Calls service method\n(e.g., GetAllAsync(userId))

note top of service
  - Contains the core business logic.
  - Builds a query to fetch data.
end note
service -> dbContext: 3. Uses DbContext to query the database

dbContext -> db: 4. Translates LINQ to SQL\nand executes query

db --> dbContext: 5. Returns raw data\n(e.g., Transaction entities)

dbContext --> service: 6. Returns EF Core entities

note top of service
  - Receives database models.
  - Maps entities to a DTO (Data Transfer Object).
  - (e.g., Transaction -> TransactionResponseDto)
end note
service --> controller: 7. Returns DTO with processed data

note top of controller
  - Wraps the DTO in a standardized `BaseResponse`.
end note
controller --> Client: 8. Sends HTTP Response\n(e.g., 200 OK with JSON body)

@enduml
